{"word":"φορμός","slug":"φορμός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φορμός</b></el> <el>(φορμός, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φέρω'><el>φέρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a basket for carrying</i> corn, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a mat</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>storea</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a seaman's cloak, of coarse plaited stuff</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a corn measure</i>, <b><a href='S:Lysias'>Lys.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}